title: Creating NIF files from SDTM data
text: Following current regulatory standards, clinical study data commonly provided SDTM format, observation-based data tabulation format logically related observations organized topical collections (domains). SDTM defined maintained Clinical Data Interchange Standards Consortium (CDISC). many exploratory analyses, data different SDTM domains need combined. example, demographic pharmacokinetic concentration data DM PC domains needed evaluate exposure age. complex analyses like population-level PK PK/PD analyses may include data, e.g., clinical laboratory, vital sign, biomarker data. NONMEM commonly used modeling software packages expect input data integrated (long) data table format strict requirements formatting nomenclature variables (see, e.g., Bauer, CPT Pharmacometrics Syst. Pharmacol. (2019) introduction). input data file analyses often casually referred ‘NONMEM input file’ ‘NIF file’, hence name package. Depending nature analysis, input variables, may easily automatically derived SDTM-formatted source data, e.g., ‘DOSE’ ‘DV’ (dependent variable pharmacokinetic observations), demographic covariates like AGE, SEX RACE. fields input data set may require study-specific considerations, example calculation baseline renal hepatic function categories, definition specific treatment conditions study arm, encoding adverse events concomitant medications interest categorical covariates. contrast latter variables often need manual study-specific data programming, core NIF data set integrates pharmacokinetic observations, drug administration information standard set baseline covariates can often generated automatically without much study-specific user input. however noted even basic NIF files, missing data points certain inconsistencies may need resolved get analysis-ready data set, particularly SDTM data stems ongoing clinical study fully cleaned yet. point later. package intended facilitate creation analysis data sets (‘NIF data sets’) SDTM-formatted clinical data. addition, includes set functions tools explore SDTM NIF data sets. first part tutorial describes import SDTM data sdtm object, explore clinical data SDTM level. second part tutorial walks generation sample NIF data set SDTM data initial exploratory analysis. tutorial contains live code depends following R packages:

title: Creating NIF files from SDTM data
text: minimum, following SDTM domains expected create basic NIF file: DM - demographic data, mostly age, sex variables per subject VS - vital signs, particularly weight height enrollment, per subject EX - exposure information administered drugs, e.g., time administration, dose, etc. PC - pharmacokinetic concentrations analytes associated administered drugs common use case, respective SDTM data files, e.g., *.sas7bdat files, copied one folder (example path//sdtm/data), can loaded using: Based , minimum required SDTM files dm.dat7bdat, vs.dat7bdat, ex.dat7bdat pc.dat7bdat. However, additional covariates AE, LB SDTM domain added, explicit list domains can provided loading function, e.g., return value function sdtm object.

code: nif_expl %>%    as.data.frame() %>%   distinct(EPOCH, ACTARMCD, ACTARM) ##                    EPOCH ACTARMCD       ACTARM ## 1 OPEN LABEL TREATMENT 1       BA Fed - Fasted ## 2 OPEN LABEL TREATMENT 2       BA Fed - Fasted ## 3 OPEN LABEL TREATMENT 1       AB Fasted - Fed ## 4 OPEN LABEL TREATMENT 2       AB Fasted - Fed nif_expl <- make_nif(sdtm_expl, silent=T) %>%   mutate(PERIOD=str_sub(EPOCH, -1, -1)) %>%    mutate(TREATMENT=str_sub(ACTARMCD, PERIOD, PERIOD)) %>%    mutate(FASTED=case_when(TREATMENT=="A" ~ 1, .default=0)) nif_expl %>%   select(USUBJID, PERIOD, TREATMENT, FASTED, TIME, EVID, AMT, ANALYTE, DV) %>%    head() ##             USUBJID PERIOD TREATMENT FASTED TIME EVID AMT    ANALYTE        DV ## 1 20230004001010001      1         B      0  0.0    1 500     RS2023        NA ## 2 20230004001010001      1         B      0  0.0    0   0     RS2023 0.0000000 ## 3 20230004001010001      1         B      0  0.0    0   0 RS2023487A 0.0000000 ## 4 20230004001010001      1         B      0  0.5    0   0     RS2023 0.7943798 ## 5 20230004001010001      1         B      0  0.5    0   0 RS2023487A 0.1463353 ## 6 20230004001010001      1         B      0  1.0    0   0     RS2023 1.9337659

title: Make a NIF data set from SDTM-formatted data — make_nif
text: ID Subject identification number TIME Recorded time administration observation events hours relative first individual event. AMT Dose administered dosing record, zero observations. DOSE Dose mg administrations post-dose observations. DV dependent variable, .e., observed concentration, zero administration records, mg/l. LNDV natural Log DV. RATE Rate infusion drug zero drug given bolus. MDV One missing DV, else zero. EVID Event ID: 0 observations, 1 administrations. CMT Pharmacokinetic compartment. set 1 administrations 2 observations. changed afterwards, needed. DTC date-time data record. FIRSTDTC Date time first event per subject. field used internally calculation TIME. Although needed NONMEM analysis, provided subsequent NIF file building steps, e.g., addition time-dependent endpoints. FIRSTADMINDTC date-time first administration respective parent drug respective subject. FIRSTTRTDTC date-time first administration parent drug respective subject. ANALYTE analyte drug data record. TRTDY treatment day, .e., relative day first treatment respective subject.
